{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017Dp6K3sB5jbSeiWdBfRmnU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The oracle script is `cases/elasticsearch/seed-hosts-repair/oracle/oracle.py`. Let me look at what it checks.\n\nKey things I notice from the test case:\n1. `cluster_prefix` defaults to `es-cluster`\n2. `http_service_name` defaults to `es-http`\n3. `expected_node_count` defaults to 3\n4. The fault is: the StatefulSet is scaled to 2, then PVC for pod 2 is deleted, then scaled back to 3. So node 2 loses its data and should rejoin.\n5. The precondition creates a ConfigMap named `es-config` with incorrect `discovery.seed_hosts` pointing to the `default` namespace instead of `elasticsearch`, which is the actual bug being tested.\n\nHowever, in the inherited case (stage_06 of the workflow), the `es_env_ready` probe detects the running pods and skips the apply step entirely, so this namespace drift never occurs. But now the `seed_hosts_index_fixture` probe is trying to reach `http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count`, and since the Elasticsearch service uses HTTPS with TLS, the HTTP request fails, triggering the apply to run and attempt to create the `app` resource.\n\nThe issue is that `app-data` already exists in the cluster and can be read via HTTPS, so the oracle should work if it's configured to use HTTPS instead. Looking at the oracle script and the test configuration, stage_06 invokes the `seed-hosts-repair` case with default parameters, which means it's using `cluster_prefix: es-cluster`, `http_service_name: es-http`, and `expected_node_count: 3`, but the actual cluster is using a different prefix.\n\nThe real cluster has a StatefulSet named `elasticsearch` with 5 nodes, not the `es-cluster` prefix and 3 nodes that the oracle is checking for. So either the oracle script is flexible enough to auto-detect the actual cluster configuration, or there's a mismatch between what the oracle expects and what's actually deployed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2826,"cache_read_input_tokens":48563,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2826},"output_tokens":42,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"53445d29-5501-4b22-8dc9-92ad7ffaa7de","uuid":"8388cdbf-ba47-4071-9292-f2c104f802a3","request_id":"req_011CcM4NyxVijAnT7EmBg1D9"}
